cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a method to solve the Joint Distribution Matching (JDM) problem, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision applications. The paper relies on optimal transport theory and Wasserstein distance to formulate the problem and proposes a novel method to solve it. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves optimization techniques, which could also place it in cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-categories.
